Bennett J. King, Appellant v. Abraham Liebeskind, et. al., Respondents. Decided March 4, 1890. Appeal from an order denying a motion of the plaintiff for an order that plaintiff have judgment against the defendant on his demurrer to the complaint as frivolous, and for *581the relief demanded in the complaint, Charles H. Smith, for appellant. Franklin Bien, for respondents.

Before Sedgwick, Ch. J., Truax and Dugro, JJ.

The pleadings were not before the general term. For that reason the Court (Per Curiam) held there was nothing to show that the court below erred, and affirmed the order.
